NLP + Deep Learning con reseas de Netflix

Anlisis de Sentimientos sobre Reseas de Netflix utilizando Procesamiento de Lenguaje Natural y Deep Learning

Dataset: netflix_reviews.csv

Autor: Alvaro Vargas

Resumen

Este cuaderno entrega NLP + Deep Learning sobre un dataset de reseas.

  • Carga inteligente (CSV/XLSX + subida en Colab) y deteccin de columnas.
  • Preprocesamiento slido (limpieza, tokenizacin robusta, stopwords, lemas/stems).
  • Nubes de palabras por clase en una sola fila (como en la captura).
  • Anlisis de n-gramas por clase y TF-IDF con top trminos.
  • Modelos clsicos (LogReg, LinearSVC) con F1 macro, matriz de confusin y anlisis de errores.
  • Tpicos (NMF) para descubrir temas latentes.
  • Deep Learning end-to-end con TextVectorization + Embedding y opcin Conv1D o BiLSTM, usando EarlyStopping, ReduceLROnPlateau y class weights.
  • Reproducibilidad (semillas, versiones) y apndice de troubleshooting (NLTK punkt_tab, etc.).

Idioma: ajust STOP_LANG = 'spanish' o 'english' en la celda de Configuracin.

Abstract / Introduccin

En este proyecto se analizarn reseas de usuarios sobre contenido de Netflix con el objetivo de explorar tcnicas de Procesamiento de Lenguaje Natural (NLP) y Deep Learning.

Los objetivos principales son:

  • Aplicar al menos dos tareas de preprocesamiento de NLP.
  • Construir una red neuronal sencilla para clasificacin de sentimientos.
  • Profundizar en una de las dos actividades para la entrega final.

Parte 1: NLP - Procesamiento de Lenguaje Natural

Dataset utilizado

Nombre: netflix_reviews.csv

Contenido: Reseas de usuarios sobre series o pelculas de Netflix.

# Utilidad: quitar caracteres invisibles (evita errores U+200B por copiado/pegado)
def strip_hidden(s: str) -> str:
    for ch in ['\u200b','\u200c','\u200d','\u200e','\u200f','\ufeff']:
        s = s.replace(ch, '')
    return s

# util unidecode con fallback (por si no est el paquete)
def _unidecode(s):
    try:
        from unidecode import unidecode
        return unidecode(s)
    except ModuleNotFoundError:
        import unicodedata
        return unicodedata.normalize("NFKD", str(s)).encode("ascii","ignore").decode("ascii")

# === Carga inteligente de datos (CSV/XLSX o subida en Colab) ===
def _smart_read(path):
    p = path.lower()
    if p.endswith(('.xlsx','.xls')):
        return pd.read_excel(path)
    else:
        try:
            return pd.read_csv(path, sep=None, engine='python')
        except UnicodeDecodeError:
            return pd.read_csv(path, sep=None, engine='python', encoding='latin1')

def load_dataframe_prefer_local(default_name='reviews.csv'):
    # a) si ya hay un DataFrame en memoria, usar el ms grande
    candidates = [v for v in globals().values() if isinstance(v, pd.DataFrame) and len(v) > 0]
    if candidates:
        return max(candidates, key=lambda d: len(d)).copy()

    # b) buscar archivos locales
    files = glob.glob("*.csv")+glob.glob("*.CSV")+glob.glob("*.xlsx")+glob.glob("*.xls")
    # priorizar nombres con 'netflix' o 'review'
    prio = [f for f in files if any(k in f.lower() for k in ['netflix','review','reviews'])]
    if prio:
        print(f"Usando archivo local: {prio[0]}")
        return _smart_read(prio[0])
    if files:
        print(f"Usando archivo local: {files[0]}")
        return _smart_read(files[0])

    # c) Colab: abrir dilogo de subida
    try:
        from google.colab import files
        print("No se encontr archivo. Sub un CSV/XLSX")
        up = files.upload()
        if not up: raise RuntimeError("No se subi ningn archivo.")
        fname = list(up.keys())[0]
        print(f"Usando archivo subido: {fname}")
        return _smart_read(fname)
    except Exception as e:
        raise AssertionError("No hay DataFrame ni archivo local. Sube un CSV/XLSX.") from e

if TEXT_COL is None:
    obj_cols = [c for c in df.columns if df[c].dtype == 'object']
    assert obj_cols, "No encuentro una columna de texto (object)."
    TEXT_COL = max(obj_cols, key=lambda c: df[c].astype(str).str.len().mean())

def basic_clean(t):
    t = _unidecode(str(t).lower())
    t = re.sub(r'http\S+|www\.\S+|\d+', ' ', t)
    t = t.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
    t = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', t).strip()
    return strip_hidden(t)

# asegurar texto limpio
if TEXT_COL != 'clean':
    df = df.copy()
    df['clean'] = df[TEXT_COL].astype(str).map(basic_clean)
    TEXT_COL = 'clean'

def to_label3(v):
    try:
        x = float(v)
        if 0 <= x <= 1:   x = 5 if x>=0.67 else (3 if x>=0.33 else 1)
        elif 0 <= x <= 10: x = 5 if x>=8   else (3 if x>=4   else 1)
    except:
        s = str(v).strip().lower()
        mapping = {'positive':5,'pos':5,'good':5,'excelente':5,'buena':5,
                   'neutral':3,'neu':3,'neutro':3,'mixed':3,
                   'negative':1,'neg':1,'bad':1,'mala':1,'terrible':1}
        x = mapping.get(s, 3)
    x = int(round(x))
    if x <= 2: return 0
    if x == 3: return 1
    return 2

y3 = df[Y_COL].map(to_label3)
classes_present = np.sort(y3.dropna().unique())
class_map = {c:i for i,c in enumerate(classes_present)}
y = y3.map(class_map).values
class_names_full = {0:'neg',1:'neu',2:'pos'}
class_names = [class_names_full[c] for c in classes_present]
num_classes = len(classes_present)

df = df.dropna(subset=[TEXT_COL, Y_COL]).reset_index(drop=True)
print(f"TEXT_COL = {TEXT_COL} | Y_COL = {Y_COL} | Clases: {class_names}")

# === Tokenizacin + clean_join (evita letras sueltas) ===
LANG = 'spanish' if STOP_LANG=='spanish' else 'english'

def tokenize_normalize(t):
    try:
        toks = word_tokenize(t, language=LANG)
    except LookupError:
        toks = re.findall(r"[A-Za-z-]+", t)
    toks = [w for w in toks if w.isalpha() and w.lower() not in stop_words and len(w) > 1]
    # lematizacin/stemming
    if STOP_LANG=='spanish' and stemmer is not None:
        toks = [stemmer.stem(w) for w in toks]
    else:
        toks = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(w) for w in toks]
    return toks

df['tokens'] = df[TEXT_COL].map(tokenize_normalize)
df['clean_join'] = df['tokens'].apply(lambda xs: ' '.join(xs))
df = df[df['clean_join'].str.strip().astype(bool)].reset_index(drop=True)
print("Muestra clean_join:", df['clean_join'].head(3).tolist())

import numpy as np
import re
from wordcloud import WordCloud

# --- 1) Asegurar columnas y limpiar bsico ---
# Cambi 'score' y 'clean_join' si tus nombres reales son otros
df = df.dropna(subset=['score', 'clean_join']).copy()
df['score'] = pd.to_numeric(df['score'], errors='coerce')
df = df.dropna(subset=['score'])

# Si sospechs que 'clean_join' qued como caracteres sueltos,
# re-limpia para evitar letras sueltas:
def fix_clean(s: str) -> str:
    s = str(s).lower()
    s = re.sub(r'http\S+|@\w+|#\w+', ' ', s)        # urls, mentions, hashtags
    s = re.sub(r'[^a-z\s]', ' ', s)         # solo letras/espacios
    s = re.sub(r'\b\w\b', ' ', s)                  # letras sueltas
    s = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', s).strip()
    return s

df['clean_join'] = df['clean_join'].astype(str).apply(fix_clean)

# --- 2) Crear la etiqueta "sentiment" dentro del df (0=neg, 1=neu, 2=pos) ---
df['sentiment'] = np.select(
    [df['score'] <= 2, df['score'] == 3, df['score'] >= 4],
    [0, 1, 2]
).astype('int8')

# --- 3) Funcin auxiliar segura para concatenar texto ---
def wc_text(frame, mask):
    s = frame.loc[mask, 'clean_join'].dropna().astype(str)
    s = s[s.str.len() > 0]
    return ' '.join(s) if not s.empty else ''

# --- 4) Textos por clase (sin usar y) ---
pos_txt = wc_text(df, df['sentiment'] == 2)
neu_txt = wc_text(df, df['sentiment'] == 1)
neg_txt = wc_text(df, df['sentiment'] == 0)

# --- 5) Plot: tres nubes en una fila ---
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(24, 8))
cfgs = [
    (pos_txt, 'Nube de Palabras - Reseas Positivas', 'viridis'),

for ax, (text, title, cmap) in zip(axes, cfgs):

# --- Top n-gramas por clase (unigramas y bigramas) SIN usar y ---
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer

# Asegurate de tener estas columnas; crea 'sentiment' si no existe (0=neg,1=neu,2=pos)
if 'sentiment' not in df.columns:
    df = df.dropna(subset=['score', 'clean_join']).copy()
    df['score'] = pd.to_numeric(df['score'], errors='coerce')
    df = df.dropna(subset=['score'])
    df['sentiment'] = np.select(
        [df['score'] <= 2, df['score'] == 3, df['score'] >= 4],
        [0, 1, 2]
    ).astype('int8')

# Nombres de clases (pods ajustar)
class_map = {0: 'Negativas', 1: 'Neutrales', 2: 'Positivas'}
class_ids = [0, 1, 2]
class_names = [class_map[c] for c in class_ids]

def top_ngrams(texts, ngram_range=(1,1), top_k=15, min_df=3):
    """
    Devuelve DataFrame con n-grama y frecuencia.
    Usa token_pattern que exige mnimo 2 caracteres para evitar letras sueltas.
    """
    if len(texts) == 0:
        return pd.DataFrame(columns=['ngram', 'freq'])
    cv = CountVectorizer(
        ngram_range=ngram_range,
        min_df=min_df,
        lowercase=True,
        token_pattern=r'(?u)\b\w\w+\b'  # evita tokens de 1 char
        # stop_words=stop_words_es  # opcional si tens lista de stopwords en ES
    )
    X = cv.fit_transform(texts)
    freqs = np.asarray(X.sum(axis=0)).ravel()
    terms = np.array(cv.get_feature_names_out())
    idx = freqs.argsort()[::-1][:top_k]
    return pd.DataFrame({'ngram': terms[idx], 'freq': freqs[idx]})

def show_bar(df_, title):
    if df_.empty:
        print(f"(sin datos) {title}")
        return
    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 5))
    # ordenar de menor a mayor para que la barra ms grande quede arriba
    df_plot = df_.sort_values('freq')
    plt.barh(df_plot['ngram'], df_plot['freq'])
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('Frecuencia')
    plt.ylabel('n-grama')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# --- Loop por clase usando df['sentiment'] ---
for cls_id, cls_name in zip(class_ids, class_names):
    texts = df.loc[df['sentiment'] == cls_id, 'clean_join'] \
              .dropna().astype(str).tolist()
    if len(texts) == 0:
        print(f"(sin textos para clase {cls_name})")
        continue

    uni = top_ngrams(texts, (1,1), top_k=15, min_df=3)
    bi  = top_ngrams(texts, (2,2), top_k=15, min_df=3)

    # Mostrar tablas cortas + grficos
    try:
        display(uni.head(10))
    except NameError:
        print("Unigramas (top 10):\n", uni.head(10), "\n")
    show_bar(uni, f"Top unigramas  {cls_name}")

    try:
        display(bi.head(10))
    except NameError:
        print("Bigramas (top 10):\n", bi.head(10), "\n")
    show_bar(bi,  f"Top bigramas  {cls_name}")

# === TF-IDF + split con y alineado ===
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, f1_score

RANDOM_STATE = 42

# 1) Asegurar 'sentiment' (0=neg,1=neu,2=pos) y texto limpio
if 'sentiment' not in df.columns:
    df = df.dropna(subset=['score', 'clean_join']).copy()
    df['score'] = pd.to_numeric(df['score'], errors='coerce')
    df = df.dropna(subset=['score'])
    df['sentiment'] = np.select(
        [df['score'] <= 2, df['score'] == 3, df['score'] >= 4],
        [0, 1, 2]
    ).astype('int8')

# 2) Mismo slice para texto y etiquetas (evita desalineaciones)
df_vec = df.loc[df['clean_join'].astype(str).str.strip().str.len() > 1, ['clean_join','sentiment']].copy()

# 3) Vectorizador (evita letras sueltas con token_pattern)
vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(
    lowercase=True,
    token_pattern=r'(?u)\b\w\w+\b',  # ignora tokens de 1 caracter
    min_df=3,
    ngram_range=(1,2),               # pods dejar (1,1) si quers solo unigramas
    max_features=50000               # opcional
)
X_tfidf = vectorizer.fit_transform(df_vec['clean_join'].astype(str))
y = df_vec['sentiment'].to_numpy()

# Chequeo de alineacin
assert X_tfidf.shape[0] == len(y), f"X={X_tfidf.shape[0]} y={len(y)} desalineados"

# 4) Split estratificado

    X_tfidf, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y
)

labels = np.sort(np.unique(y))

    "LinearSVC": LinearSVC()
}

for name, clf in classic_models.items():
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
    print(f"\n== {name} ==")
    # Usar 'labels' para que coincida con target_names aunque falte alguna clase
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, labels=labels, target_names=target_names, digits=3))
    f1m = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average='macro')
    print(f"F1 macro: {f1m:.3f}")
    print("Matriz de confusin:\n", confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, labels=labels))
    reports[name] = {'f1_macro': f1m}

# === NMF sobre TF-IDF (tpicos) ===
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.decomposition import NMF

# 1) Asegurar el acceso a los nombres de features del mismo vectorizador de X_tfidf
try:
    feat_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
except NameError:
    # Por si lo llamaste 'tfidf' en otro lado
    feat_names = tfidf.get_feature_names_out()

# 2) Ajuste de NMF
num_topics = 8
nmf = NMF(
    n_components=num_topics,
    random_state=RANDOM_STATE,
    init='nndsvd',
    max_iter=400
)
W = nmf.fit_transform(X_tfidf)  # (n_docs  n_topics)
H = nmf.components_             # (n_topics  n_features)
print(f"Reconstruction error: {nmf.reconstruction_err_:.4f}")

# 3) Mostrar trminos top por tpico
def show_topics(H, feat_names, topn=10, return_frames=True):
    topic_frames = []
    for i, comp in enumerate(H):
        idx = np.argsort(comp)[::-1][:topn]
        terms = [feat_names[j] for j in idx]
        weights = comp[idx]
        print(f"Tpico {i}: {', '.join(terms)}")
        if return_frames:
            topic_frames.append(pd.DataFrame({'term': terms, 'weight': weights}))
    return topic_frames if return_frames else None

topic_frames = show_topics(H, feat_names, topn=10, return_frames=True)

# 4) (Opcional) Graficar top trminos por tpico
def plot_topic_terms(df_terms, topic_id, topn=None):
    dfp = df_terms.copy()
    if topn is not None:
        dfp = dfp.iloc[:topn]
    dfp = dfp.sort_values('weight')  # para barh ascendente
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
    plt.barh(dfp['term'], dfp['weight'])
    plt.title(f"Tpico {topic_id}  trminos ms pesados")
    plt.xlabel("Peso en el componente (H)")
    plt.ylabel("Trmino")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Ejemplo: graficar los 10 trminos principales de cada tpico
for k, dfk in enumerate(topic_frames):
    plot_topic_terms(dfk, k, topn=10)

# 5) (Opcional) Asignar tpico dominante por documento
# Si antes creaste df_vec para X_tfidf, lo reutilizamos; si no, lo regeneramos desde df
try:
    df_vec
except NameError:
    # crear df_vec consistente con X_tfidf (mismo filtro que usaste para vectorizar)
    mask_valid = df['clean_join'].astype(str).str.strip().str.len() > 1
    df_vec = df.loc[mask_valid, ['clean_join']].reset_index(drop=True).copy()

df_vec['topic'] = W.argmax(axis=1)
df_vec['topic_score'] = W.max(axis=1)

# 6) (Opcional) Inspeccionar documentos ms representativos de cada tpico
def top_docs_for_topic(W, df_texts, topic_id, k=5):
    idx = np.argsort(W[:, topic_id])[::-1][:k]
    return df_texts.iloc[idx].assign(score=W[idx, topic_id])

# Ejemplo: ver 3 docs top del tpico 0
top3_t0 = top_docs_for_topic(W, df_vec[['clean_join']], topic_id=0, k=3)

DL end-to-end (TextVectorization + Embedding)

# === Deep Learning end-to-end: TextVectorization + Embedding ===
X_text = df[TEXT_COL].astype(str).values

Xtr, Xte, ytr, yte = train_test_split(X_text, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y)

max_tokens = 20000
seq_len    = 200
embedding_dim = 64

textvec = layers.TextVectorization(max_tokens=max_tokens, output_mode='int', output_sequence_length=seq_len)
textvec.adapt(tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(Xtr).batch(256))

# Cambi estas flags para explorar arquitecturas
USE_CONV1D = True
USE_BILSTM = False

inp = tf.keras.Input(shape=(1,), dtype=tf.string)
x = textvec(inp)
x = layers.Embedding(max_tokens, embedding_dim)(x)

if USE_BILSTM:
    x = layers.Bidirectional(layers.LSTM(64, return_sequences=False))(x)
elif USE_CONV1D:
    x = layers.Conv1D(128, 5, padding='same', activation='relu')(x)
    x = layers.GlobalMaxPooling1D()(x)
else:
    x = layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D()(x)

x = layers.Dense(64, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.Dropout(0.3)(x)
out = layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')(x)

dl_model = keras_models.Model(inp, out)
dl_model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
dl_model.summary()

# Class weights
cw = compute_class_weight('balanced', classes=np.arange(num_classes), y=ytr)
class_weight = {i: w for i, w in enumerate(cw)}
print("Class weights:", class_weight)

cbs = [
    callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', patience=3, restore_best_weights=True),
    callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.5, patience=2, min_lr=1e-5, verbose=1)
]

hist = dl_model.fit(
    Xtr, ytr,
    validation_data=(Xte, yte),
    epochs=10, batch_size=64,
    class_weight=class_weight,
    callbacks=cbs, verbose=1
)

# Curvas
H = pd.DataFrame(hist.history)
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5)); plt.plot(H['accuracy'], label='acc_train'); plt.plot(H['val_accuracy'], label='acc_val')
plt.title('Accuracy'); plt.xlabel('poca'); plt.ylabel('Accuracy'); plt.legend(); plt.show()
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5)); plt.plot(H['loss'], label='loss_train'); plt.plot(H['val_loss'], label='loss_val')
plt.title('Loss'); plt.xlabel('poca'); plt.ylabel('Loss'); plt.legend(); plt.show()

# === Funcin de inferencia rpida ===
idx2name = {i:n for i,n in enumerate(class_names)}
def predict_texts(texts):
    arr = np.array(list(map(str, texts)))
    probs = dl_model.predict(arr, batch_size=64, verbose=0)
    labels = probs.argmax(axis=1)
    return pd.DataFrame({
        'texto': texts,
        'pred': [idx2name[i] for i in labels],
        'p_neg': probs[:, class_names.index('neg')] if 'neg' in class_names else np.nan,
        'p_neu': probs[:, class_names.index('neu')] if 'neu' in class_names else np.nan,
        'p_pos': probs[:, class_names.index('pos')] if 'pos' in class_names else np.nan,
    })

# --- Comparativa de modelos: Clsicos (TF-IDF) vs DL ---
import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report

# Variables de entrada esperadas:
# - df, TEXT_COL (columna de texto)
# - y (etiquetas 0..C-1)
# - dl_model ya entrenado + el split Xte y yte OR Xtr, Xte, ytr, yte
assert 'df' in globals() and 'TEXT_COL' in globals() and 'y' in globals()

# 1) Preparar texto
X_text = df[TEXT_COL].astype(str).values
X_tr_clf, X_te_clf, y_tr_clf, y_te_clf = train_test_split(
    X_text, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y
)

# 2) TF-IDF + modelos lineales

    "LogisticRegression": LogisticRegression(max_iter=2000, n_jobs=-1),
    "LinearSVC": LinearSVC()
}.items():
    clf.fit(Xtr_v, y_tr_clf)
    y_hat = clf.predict(Xte_v)
    res.append({
        "Modelo": name + " (TF-IDF)",
        "Accuracy": accuracy_score(y_te_clf, y_hat),
        "F1_macro": f1_score(y_te_clf, y_hat, average='macro')
    })

# 3) DL end-to-end (usa tu modelo ya entrenado)

    X_dl = Xte
    y_dl = yte
else:
    X_dl = X_te_clf
    y_dl = y_te_clf

# === F1 por longitud del texto (celda autnoma y robusta) ===
import numpy as np, pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, accuracy_score

assert 'df' in globals() and 'TEXT_COL' in globals() and 'y' in globals(), \
    "Necesito df, TEXT_COL y y (etiquetas 0..C-1)."
assert 'dl_model' in globals(), "Necesito dl_model ya entrenado."

# 1) Split para CLSICO si no existe
if not all(k in globals() for k in ['X_tr_clf','X_te_clf','y_tr_clf','y_te_clf']):
    X_text_all = df[TEXT_COL].astype(str).values
    X_tr_clf, X_te_clf, y_tr_clf, y_te_clf = train_test_split(
        X_text_all, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y
    )

# 2) TF-IDF + LogReg (baseline clsico) si no existe
if 'tfidf' not in globals() or 'best_clf' not in globals():
    tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=8000, ngram_range=(1,2), min_df=5)
    Xtr_v = tfidf.fit_transform(X_tr_clf)
    Xte_v = tfidf.transform(X_te_clf)
    best_clf = LogisticRegression(max_iter=2000, n_jobs=-1).fit(Xtr_v, y_tr_clf)
    y_pred_clf = best_clf.predict(Xte_v)
else:
    # Si ya exista, aseguro matrices
    Xtr_v = tfidf.transform(X_tr_clf) if 'Xtr_v' not in globals() else Xtr_v
    Xte_v = tfidf.transform(X_te_clf)
    y_pred_clf = best_clf.predict(Xte_v)

# 3) Bins por longitud (CLSICO)
lengths = pd.Series([len(t) for t in X_te_clf])
q1, q2 = lengths.quantile([0.33, 0.66])
bins_c = pd.cut(lengths, [-1, q1, q2, lengths.max()], labels=['short','medium','long'])

rows_c = []
for seg, mask in [('short', bins_c=='short'), ('medium', bins_c=='medium'), ('long', bins_c=='long')]:
    if mask.sum()==0: continue
    rows_c.append({
        "segmento": seg,
        "n": int(mask.sum()),
        "F1_Clsico": f1_score(y_te_clf[mask], y_pred_clf[mask], average='macro'),
        "Acc_Clsico": accuracy_score(y_te_clf[mask], y_pred_clf[mask]),
    })
classic_df = pd.DataFrame(rows_c)
display(classic_df.style.format({"F1_Clsico":"{:.3f}","Acc_Clsico":"{:.3f}"}).set_caption("F1/Acc por longitud  Clsico (TF-IDF + LogReg)"))

# 4) Predicciones DL (usa tu split de arriba si no tens Xte/yte)
if 'Xte' in globals() and 'yte' in globals():
    X_dl, y_dl = Xte, yte
else:
    X_dl, y_dl = X_te_clf, y_te_clf

y_prob_dl = dl_model.predict(X_dl, batch_size=128, verbose=0)
y_pred_dl = y_prob_dl.argmax(axis=1)

# Bins por longitud (DL)
lengths_dl = pd.Series([len(t) for t in X_dl])
q1d, q2d = lengths_dl.quantile([0.33, 0.66])
bins_d = pd.cut(lengths_dl, [-1, q1d, q2d, lengths_dl.max()], labels=['short','medium','long'])

rows_d = []
for seg, mask in [('short', bins_d=='short'), ('medium', bins_d=='medium'), ('long', bins_d=='long')]:
    if mask.sum()==0: continue
    rows_d.append({
        "segmento": seg,

        "F1_DL": f1_score(y_dl[mask], y_pred_dl[mask], average='macro'),
        "Acc_DL": accuracy_score(y_dl[mask], y_pred_dl[mask]),
    })
dl_df = pd.DataFrame(rows_d)
display(dl_df.style.format({"F1_DL":"{:.3f}","Acc_DL":"{:.3f}"}).set_caption("F1/Acc por longitud  DL (TextVectorization+Embedding)"))

En la etapa de profundizacin se opt por Deep Learning, evaluando desempeo, matriz de confusin, anlisis de errores e inferencia sobre textos nuevos.

Hallazgos de exploracin.

Las nubes y los top n-gramas por clase evidencian vocabulario distintivo entre reseas positivas, neutrales y negativas; ocultar trminos de marca evit sesgos visuales. El NMF separ temas interpretables (p. ej., actuaciones, guion, ritmo, gnero), y la inspeccin de documentos con mayor topic_score ayud a validar cada tpico.

Conclusin tcnica.

El flujo completo, desde el preprocesamiento hasta la inferencia, queda ordenado, reproducible y con soporte de visualizaciones. Los modelos lineales con TF-IDF brindan una base fuerte y explicable; el pipeline DL end-to-end proporciona un salto de capacidad sin depender de ingeniera de features manual, y resulta especialmente til cuando se busca generalizar sobre redacciones heterogneas.

Limitaciones.

Posible desbalance entre clases, variacin lxica (ES/EN/mixto) y dependencia de la calidad del texto. No se realiz ajuste fino de umbrales ni calibracin de probabilidades para ranking.
